Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a small #pot{} over medium heat. Stir in @turmeric{1/4%tsp} (1/2 tsp for 4 servings) until combined.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4), and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to use in step 5.

Meanwhile, bring @butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Dice @roma tomato{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp}, @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Add water 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @ground turkey{10%oz}, @shawarma spice blend{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{3} and 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4). Reduce heat to medium low and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @sliced almonds{1/2%oz} and half the scallion greens. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Toast @whole wheat pitas{2}. Spread with softened @butter{2%tbsp}; cut each pita into four pieces.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with turkey and tomato in separate sections; sprinkle tomato with a pinch of salt. Drizzle turkey with @hot sauce{2%tsp} to taste. Drizzle white sauce over bowls; garnish with remaining scallion greens. Serve with pitas and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> TIP: If you like, scoop up some of the rice, turkey, tomato, and sauces with the pita and eat it all in one bite!